[Although the report indicates that the number of suspected cases of chikungunya virus infection is climbing, there is no mention of the numbers of cases that are occurring. This is doubtless complicated by the simultaneous occurrence of dengue cases in this mixed outbreak. Chikungunya virus infections are characterized by acute joint pain that may persist for weeks or even months, and may incapacitate affected individuals. Interestingly, a mixed dengue/chikungunya virus outbreak has been reported currently going on in Antique province, Philippines (http://www.tempo.com.ph/2013/07/chikungunya-dengue-have-same-symptoms/#.UdWSBDu-2So).

A map showing the location of the Philippines can be accessed at http://www.mapsofworld.com/philippines/maps/Philippines-Location.jpg. A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the Tabuk city in Kalinga province can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/7v7W. - Mod.TY]
